        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/000/777/332/original/5d052f95-d20c-4c0b-9880-5a0dd5cdffb6.png" srcset="" alt="Open Student Submission" height="387" width="357">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_7FF1ADC0-22E2-0135-8D26-22000BC102FE" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Use the <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-use-the-student-list-to-view-student-submissions-in/ta-p/770" target="_blank">student list</a> to locate a student submission.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="view_rubric" data-step-uuid="D56F0DE3-676A-4481-990D-C3D18D3C4B32">
    <h2 id="view_rubric" class="step-title screensteps-heading">View Rubric</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/000/777/330/original/eac7774a-96c6-424d-ac58-d6df6fb28855.png" srcset="" alt="View Rubric" height="147" width="179">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_7FF1D9F0-22E2-0135-8D28-22000BC102FE" class="text-block-content">
    <p>Click the <strong>View Rubric</strong> button.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
        <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-2" id="resize_rubric" data-step-uuid="02e3a680-ca69-4239-930f-6e8cbcb3b2ab">
    <h3 id="resize_rubric" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Resize Rubric</h3>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/002/098/670/original/894608c1-fa95-42a4-a33c-052ebc72e775.png" srcset="" alt="Resize Rubric" height="646" width="738">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_7FF207D0-22E2-0135-8D2A-22000BC102FE" class="text-block-content">
    <p>To view the entire rubric window, you may need to scroll both vertically and horizontally. To resize the rubric window, click and drag the sizing column horizontally.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="complete_rubric" data-step-uuid="040C109B-4E6B-4357-B487-8B836AFE890D">
    <h2 id="complete_rubric" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Complete Rubric</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/002/098/672/original/97d453c1-24e8-418c-b6ca-7c2acfb7b37c.png" srcset="" alt="Complete Rubric" height="646" width="706">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_7FF23300-22E2-0135-8D2C-22000BC102FE" class="text-block-content">
    <p>In the Ratings column, enter a comment for the criterion [1]. If you want to save the comment to use again for other students, select the <strong>Save this comment for reuse</strong> checkbox [2]. </p>
<p>In the points column, enter a score for the criterion [3]. Each score will create the total points for the assignment [4]. </p>
  </div>
</div>
 
        <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-2" id="reuse_comments" data-step-uuid="b3538a93-2c9a-41e5-9a42-0e8c128a25c8">
    <h3 id="reuse_comments" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Reuse Comments</h3>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/002/098/665/original/158c0d1c-8a9f-40b3-b761-905ef1ef5ef7.png" srcset="" alt="Reuse Comments" height="692" width="707">
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_7FF26070-22E2-0135-8D2E-22000BC102FE" class="text-block-content">
    <p>If you select your comment for reuse, in your next student assessment, the comment displays as an option in a comments drop-down menu. </p>
<p><strong>Note: </strong>Comments saved for reuse cannot be edited or deleted.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>
 
  </div>

      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="save_rubric" data-step-uuid="ad6c9ca5-176d-4214-8f14-a03d3e4a1880">
